activities:
General Dynamics Corporate Headquarters (excluding subsidiaries)  processes Personal Data concerning company personnel for one or more of the following purposes:
-Recruitment, including general recruitment, enabling existing employees to apply for vacancies;
-Compensation planning, succession-planning, and administering payroll and employee benefits plans and programs;
-Managing HR programs, including talent management, expense reimbursement, travel, company credit cards, tax equalization, and employee relocations;
-Evaluating employee conduct and performance and implementing employment-related actions and decisions; 
-Implementing security programs and policies, security clearance requirements, and complying with laws and regulations;
-Granting and managing access to, and monitoring the use of, Company assets, including computer networks and information systems; 
-Implementing and administering the Company's ethics program and hotline, and other internal controls and audit procedures; 
-Cooperating with law enforcement and other governmental agencies, complying with legal reporting requirements, and with investigations and legal proceedings; and
-Other lawful and reasonable purposes permitted by applicable laws.
